HEADWORD: Aristotype
<hw>A*ris"to*type`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ best +
<ets>-type</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>Orig., a printing-out
process using paper coated with silver chloride in gelatin; now, any
such process using silver salts in either collodion or gelatin; also, a
print so made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

